article.description: Boubacar Toure had 17 points as Eastern Michigan defeated Western Michigan 69-51 on Saturday.
article.headline: Toure's 17 points help Eastern Michigan top Western Michigan
article.linkText: Toure's 17 points help Eastern Michigan top Western Michigan
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. -- Boubacar Toure had 17 points as Eastern Michigan defeated Western Michigan 69-51 on Saturday. Chris James and Noah Morgan added 15 points each and Darion Spottsville scored 10 for the Eagles (14-11, 4-8 Mid-American Conference). Brandon Johnson had 17 points and seven rebounds and Michael Flowers scored 10 points for the Broncos (11-14, 4-8). Eastern Michigan takes on Kent State at home on Tuesday.
